Ad Text:
About Us 
At EnergyAustralia our shared purpose is to lead and accelerate the clean energy transformation for all. We seek to do this by making energy simple for our customers, meeting their needs by combining their assets into our flexible energy portfolio. 


About the Team 
The Customer Transformation Team is a program of work that has been established to transform the way the Customer business operates. The challenge for this newly formed team is to ensure our delivery is purposeful & sustainable in the short term and drives a competitive value proposition for our customers in the long term. 


About the role  
As Risk Analyst, you will play a key role in the successful delivery of EnergyAustralia’s Customer Transformation Program by embedding proactive, enterprise-aligned risk management practices. Working closely with business leaders, this role delivers value by providing analytical insights, uplifting risk and issue management maturity, embedding strong risk governance, and enabling the successful execution of major transformation initiatives.  Key elements of the role include (but aren’t limited to): 


Program Risk Management 

Identifying, assessing and monitoring risk across the Customer Transformation Program. 
Facilitating the risk management process with program streams, including risk workshops and risk reviews.  
Developing risk dashboards and analytics which unlock insights and informed decision-making. 
Driving positive risk behaviours across the program through risk training and capability support. 


Program Issues Management 

Supporting the identification, documentation, and tracking of program-level issues. 
Assisting in the development and maintenance of program issues register and reporting tools. 
 

Stakeholder Relationships 

Building strong working relationships with program leaders, risk owners, mitigation owners, and business unit stakeholders to support effective risk and issues management.  
Acting as a trusted advisor by providing clear, actionable risk insights that support strategic decision-making and program delivery. 
Collaborating with the Enterprise Risk Team to ensure alignment with EnergyAustralia’s Risk Management Policy, appetites, and reporting standards. 


Reporting & Risk Governance


Ensuring compliance with internal PMO governance standards and reporting requirements, includes risk and issues governance. 
Delivering accurate and timely risk reporting for program leadership and governance forums. 


About you 
We are looking for a savvy, self-sufficient risk professional who will be excited by the opportunity to come in and support our risk leader and contribute to a truly transformative program of work. You’ll be analytical by nature and be comfortable managing a host of tactical activities, leaning on your technical risk expertise combined with your ability to build credible relationships. Other elements we’d love to see include: 

3-5 years’ experience in risk management, preferably within complex business/organisational structures, large-scale transformation, or customer-focused programs. 
Strong experience in risk management technical processes, enterprise risk frameworks (e.g. ISO 31000) and three lines of defence model. 
Experience using and building risk management tools or systems (e.g., risk registers, dashboards, reporting platforms). 
Adaptability, allowing you to adjust priorities to meet changing business needs. 
Proven ability to independently identify problems and drive effective resolution without prompting. 
Relevant tertiary qualification, such as Engineering or Business Analytics. 
Governance, Risk and Compliance (GRC) Certifications from industry or governance bodies, optional but highly advantageous. 
 


Why Us?
EnergyAustralia is a place where all employees are genuinely valued, supported, and free to be themselves — because we believe that’s when we’re at our best. 

We embrace diversity of background, experience, and perspective, and we encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, people with disability, and those from the LGBTQ+ community. Here's what you can look forward to:

Employee discounts on electricity and gas, plus savings on major brands and products. 
20 weeks’ paid parental leave – completely gender-equal. 
Energise Program – flexible working that’s team-centric, enabling teams to agree and succeed together.
Performance recognition and incentive programs – tailored to different roles and teams to reward great work throughout the year.
Supportive leaders and a down-to-earth culture where you can be your authentic self. 


If you’re ready to ‘light the way’ in your career, click ‘Apply’ to submit your confidential application. Please note this is a 12-month fixed-term opportunity.

Job Title: Lead Business Analyst - Human-Centred Aged Care Reform
Ad Text:
We are looking to engage a skilled Lead Business Analyst to join our Federal Government client undertaking a program of aged care reform!



Our Federal Government Client is currently looking for a Lead Business Analyst to join their team on a long term engagement.



Australian Citizens with Baseline security clearance will be regarded for this role.



This is your chance to make a difference for our Federal Government client in this 7 month contract with a 12 months extension option.



This is a unique opportunity to apply your deep understanding of human-centred design (HCD) and service design to create digital products and services that genuinely meet the needs of older Australians and their providers. You will lead a team dedicated to designing and delivering solutions that are not only functional but also intuitive, accessible, and empathetic.



As the Lead Business Analyst, you will be at the forefront of the design process, responsible for translating complex policy and user needs into tangible digital solutions. Your primary responsibilities will include:




Owning Human-Centred Design: Embed HCD and service design principles into all stages of the delivery process, ensuring the user's voice is central to every decision.
Leading a Team: Lead, mentor, and guide a dedicated team of business analysts, ensuring the delivery of high-quality analysis and requirements.
Domain Immersion: Develop an intricate knowledge of the aged care sector, becoming a subject matter expert on critical systems such as the Aged Care Gateway and the Government Provider Management System.
Stakeholder Collaboration: Work closely with Architects, Product Managers, SES-level business owners, and other stakeholders to define iterative work packages and ensure alignment on project goals.
Driving Delivery: Play a key leadership role within a multidisciplinary design team to ensure artefacts meet agreed scope, quality standards, and delivery timeframes



To be considered for this opportunity, APPLY to this advertisement.

For more information about the role, contact BADRE on (02) 5109 0933.





If you are unsuccessful in this application, with your permission we would like to keep you in consideration for future roles that may suit you better.

Job Title: Principal Data Analyst / Sydney / Permanent / $150k to $170k + super
Ad Text:
Principal Data Analyst / Sydney / Permanent / $150k to $170k + super

About the company

Our client is a growing Australian consumer-focused business, leveraging data to drive strategy and innovation. With a focus on scaling operations and enhancing customer outcomes, they are committed to building a future shaped by analytics and advanced technology.

About the role

Based in Sydney CBD, the Principal Data Analyst will report to senior leadership and lead analysis of complex, high-volume consumer datasets. Partnering with leaders and technical teams, the role delivers impact through advanced modelling, SQL development, and data visualisation. 

Benefits

Salary range of $150k to $170k + super (depending on experience)
Learning and development opportunities in advanced analytics and ML
Exposure to enterprise-level projects with tangible impact

Develop and optimise SQL queries across large datasets
Build and refine machine learning models to deliver insights
Design and deliver dashboards in Tableau or Power BI
Translate complex data into clear recommendations for stakeholders

Strong expertise in SQL and data modelling
Experience with ML techniques and predictive modelling
Skilled in Tableau or Power BI for reporting and insights
Proven ability to analyse large transactional datasets
Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills
If you’re interested in this opportunity and feel you’re the right fit please click “apply”

Allura Partners was founded to support private equity firms by placing C-Suites to lead, transform, and scale portfolio companies. Today, in addition to our proven private equity specialisation, we’ve become a trusted partner for major ASX-listed and private enterprises in Australia, offering executive search, recruitment, and business transformation. We connect businesses and top-tier talent, exceeding expectations and driving lasting impact.

Principal Data Analyst / Sydney / Permanent / $150k to $170k + super

Proven experience as a Business Analyst in an IT service delivery or support environment.

Minimum 3-4 years of Business Analyst experience in IT service delivery is required.

Excellent communication, stakeholder engagement, and documentation skills.

Desirable Skills

Experience working within Australian Government departments or agencies.

Familiarity with Agile methodologies and tools (e.g., JIRA, Confluence).

Exposure to enterprise systems, cloud platforms, or digital transformation projects.

Our Queensland Government client is seeking an experienced and collaborative BI Systems Analyst to join Data Analytics & Reporting Services (DARS) within Road Safety Systems Program. Working closely with the Project Manager and Solution Architects, you will bring a a balanced set of skills between traditional business and systems analysis and hands on expertise in using BI tools such as Tableau and Power BI to generate visualisations and reports.

Initially the role will be more focused on requirements, business processes and designing the new platform including selection of tools. As the platform is developed the role will shift to have a more hands on data analytics focus to establish capability and embed the use of the tools and processes.

Skills required
• Ability to conduct requirements gathering and design workshops with business users including documenting functional requirements, user stories, source system data feeds, data flows, business rules, and data conversion/standardisation requirements.
• Experience in developing visualisations of data for analytics and canned reports using BI tools such as Tableau, Power BI, Splunk.
• Experience sourcing data from various types of on premise and cloud database systems, for example: Oracle, Postgres, SQL Server, AWS Analytics, AWS Redshift, Azure Synapse, Snowflake.
• Experience with the suite of AWS Analytics, Reporting and Monitoring Tools.
• Ability to run training and knowledge transfer sessions in the use of BI tools.
• Ability to assess user needs and change impacts related to current and future state solutions and determine the activities required to assist users through the change and transition process.

Highly Desirable
• Experience working with Geospatial data and cloud environments.
• Experience in the public sector or large organisations.
• Experience working on modernisation and transformational projects, including Agile and hybrid delivery approaches.

Closing Date: 28 October 2025

For more information, please contact Angela Anderson at angela.a@edenritchie.com.au

Company Description


Join the team redefining how the world experiences design.

Hey, g'day, mabuhay, kia ora, 你好, hallo, vítejte!

Thanks for stopping by. We know job hunting can be a little time consuming and you're probably keen to find out what's on offer, so we'll get straight to the point.

Where and how you can work

Our flagship campus is in Sydney. We also have a campus in Melbourne and co-working spaces in Brisbane, Perth and Adelaide. But you have choice in where and how you work, we trust our Canvanauts to choose the balance that empowers them and their team to achieve their goals.

About Content Studio

The Content Studio group operates at the intersection of human creativity, quality, and emerging technology. We’re on a mission to empower the world to design by building a world-class, personalised, AI-driven design experience for our users. Our work expands content acquisition, creation and discovery as well as unlocking design product experiences that helps every user, everywhere to bring their ideas to life.

Sitting in the Content Studio group, the GenAI Studio Strategy Lead will help lead the newly established GenAI Studio subgroup, whose mission is to make Canva’s AI-design experience world class quality. In partnership with Design, Product and Engineering teams, you’ll help to imagine, build, improve and refine Canva’s AI-powered design products. You’ll collaborate with multiple teams right across the Canva AI ecosystem, and, together with a Design Lead, lead a creative team who will be the ‘designers in the loop’ for Canva’s AI products and tooling – responsible for design production and review, tooling review, and craft consultancy.

What you’ll do

As Strategy Lead, you bring expertise in strategy, business management (incl. budget ownership), leadership and cross-functional stakeholder management. In particular, you will:

Drive strategic and operational excellence within your group or subgroup, translating high-level vision into actionable roadmaps and execution plans.
Own budgeting and performance metrics tracking, developing data-driven insights and reporting frameworks that inform strategic decision-making and ensure alignment on priorities across your group or subgroup.
Act as a strategic partner to senior leadership to identify growth opportunities, operational bottlenecks, and strategic initiatives that drive business impact.
Lead cross-functional initiatives, coordinating with Design, Product, Engineering, Marketing, Growth, and other specialties to deliver complex strategic outcomes.
Support organisational scaling by designing and implementing operational processes, tools, and frameworks that enable team growth.
Lead strategic planning and execution of cross-group company goals, driving alignment on long-term vision and resource prioritisation.
Lead cross-functional groups or subgroups to execute against their vision and strategic priorities.

What we're looking for

We're seeking a strategic thinker who thrives in fast-paced environments and can seamlessly bridge the gap between high-level strategy and hands-on execution. You should be someone who naturally gravitates toward solving complex problems, enjoys working with data to drive decisions, and can build strong relationships in a collaborative and cross-functional environment. The ideal candidate combines analytical rigour with creative problem-solving, demonstrating both the ability to develop comprehensive strategies and the operational excellence to execute them flawlessly.

Minimum 5-7+ years of experience with demonstrated strategic and operational leadership
In-house experience within high-growth content, media or marketplace technology companies
Proven track record of driving strategic objectives from conception to execution, with measurable business impact
Strong analytical and quantitative skills, with experience in data analysis, performance measurement, and budget ownership
Excellent communication and stakeholder management abilities, with experience partnering with senior leadership and owning cross-functional initiatives
Strong business acumen and understanding of content or technology industry dynamics

What's in it for you?

Achieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard - and we do - but you'll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity and fun woven throughout life at Canva, too. We also offer a range of benefits to set you up for every success in and outside of work.

Here's a taste of what's on offer:

Equity packages - we want our success to be yours too
Inclusive parental leave policy that supports all parents & carers
An annual Vibe & Thrive allowance to support your wellbeing, social connection, office setup & more
Flexible leave options that empower you to be a force for good, take time to recharge and supports you personally

Check out lifeatcanva.com for more info.

Other stuff to know

We make hiring decisions based on your experience, skills and passion, as well as how you can enhance Canva and our culture. When you apply, please tell us the pronouns you use and any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process.

We celebrate all types of skills and backgrounds at Canva so even if you don’t feel like your skills quite match what’s listed above - we still want to hear from you!

Please note that interviews are conducted virtually.

Join an organisation where curiosity is encouraged, ideas are valued, and the potential of AI is being unlocked every day.

Apply now!

Our client is a leading financial services organisation undergoing a significant transformation journey. With a strong focus on innovation, simplification and operational excellence, they are reshaping how the business delivers value to customers and stakeholders.

This role presents an exciting opportunity to join a high-performing finance team and play a pivotal role in driving the success of major transformation and integration programs across the organisation.

As Senior Manager, Program Finance, you will provide strategic financial leadership, analysis and governance across multiple transformation programs.
You’ll partner with senior leaders across Finance, Technology and Business divisions to ensure effective financial management, oversight and benefits realisation of key investment initiatives. The role also supports the CFO and Head of Transformation Finance with in-depth expense analysis, forecasting and performance reporting to ensure financial transparency and accountability across all programs.

Key Responsibilities
• Lead program-level financial governance, reporting and forecasting for large-scale transformation initiatives.
• Partner with Program Directors, Finance and Business stakeholders to manage budgets, track benefits and deliver financial insights.
• Provide analytical support and scenario modelling for investment decisions and strategic planning.
• Deliver clear, data-driven insights and executive-level reporting to steering committees and senior leadership.
• Oversee financial controls, project expense management and month-end processes.
• Support productivity and cost optimisation initiatives, including cost-to-serve metrics and OKR tracking.
• Partner with IT and operational teams to quantify transformation benefits and track realisation.
• Drive continuous improvement in financial processes and reporting efficiency.
• Mentor and develop team members to enhance analytical and commercial capability.

You will be an experienced finance professional with strong commercial and analytical capability, and a proven ability to work across complex programs in transformation environments. You can balance strategic oversight with hands-on delivery and are comfortable engaging with senior stakeholders.

Key Requirements:
• Degree in Accounting or Finance, with CA/CPA (or equivalent) qualification.
• 10+ years’ experience in financial planning and analysis, commercial finance, or transformation program finance.
• Proven background supporting large-scale transformation or integration programs.
• Experience in financial services, insurance, or other complex corporate environments.
• Strong skills in financial governance, investment appraisal, and benefit tracking.
• Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills.
• Demonstrated ability to simplify complex financial information and provide actionable insights.

What’s on Offer:
• Strategic, high-impact role at the centre of a major transformation agenda.
• Opportunity to influence executive-level decision making.
• Collaborative, flexible, and high-performing culture.
• Competitive remuneration

Join Sitzler Pty Ltd, a leading construction company, as a Financial Planning and Analysis Manager based in our Berrimah Office. This is an exciting opportunity to lead the finance team in the 'Accounting & Finance' department. If you are an experienced professional looking for a 'Permanent - Full Time' position with a passion for financial planning and analysis, we want to hear from you!




Main Purpose of the Role:

To leads Sitzler's financial planning, budgeting, and forecasting processes to support strategic decision-making and drive performance and growth. Key responsibilities include overseeing budgets, performing financial analysis, creating financial models and forecasts, monitoring performance, and providing actionable insights to the Executive Leadership Team (ELT). The role requires strong analytical skills, technical proficiency in financial software, and effective collaboration with various business stakeholders.

Key Responsibilities:

Includes but not limited to the following: 

Budgeting and Forecasting:

Lead the development of annual budgets and quarterly forecasts for revenues, profits, expenses, and cash flow. Including updating Sitzler’s financial model as required.

Develop ownership and a detailed level of understanding across cash flow across projects and the total organisation, balance sheet metrics and working capital drivers. This includes debt and bonding outlook and capacity. 

Develop a financial Risk and Opportunity register in-conjunction with the CFO and ELT.

Strategic Planning: 

Provide financial insights and recommendations to support long-term financial health and strategic business decisions for Sitzler’s 3 year plan.

This includes maintaining all key data inputs into the model to guarantee the integrity of the model outputs. Also working with key stakeholders to develop accurate pipeline and orderbook information as well as overhead costs plus future resource planning.

Maintain the financial Risk and Opportunity register in-conjunction with the CFO and ELT.

Strategic Decision Support:

Business Partner with CFO, EMT and business units to evaluate financial implications of strategic initiatives, investments, and projects.

Conduct scenario analysis to further assess potential risks and opportunities impact on Sitzler’s financial outlook for downside and upside scenarios, potential mergers and acquisitions (including for ESG reporting requirements).

Provide recommendations to optimise resource allocation and improve profitability.

Process Improvement:

Streamline and automate financial reporting and planning processes to improve efficiency and accuracy.

Implement best practices in financial analysis and forecasting.

Collaborate with IT and other departments to enhance financial systems tools and data extraction

Financial Analysis and Reporting:

Analyse financial performance, including variance analysis of actuals vs. budget/forecast. Including improvement the commentary for Sitzler’s portfolio of projects and business unit performance.

Identify key performance indicators (KPIs) and provide actionable insights to improve financial outcomes. This includes working with the new Business Analytics team on creating a regular cadence and a set suite of reports, identifying exceptions and working with stakeholders to implement change as a result of your findings.

People and Stakeholders

The role is a key manager role within the Finance and Administration team

As a manager the FP&A Manager provides wider support to finance team with respect to month end reporting, half year and full year statutory reporting and ad-hoc requests from the Finance team lead.

The role is to primarily business partner to the CFO in completing all key budgeting, forecasting and strategic planning activities. In addition, this includes strategic and ad-hoc projects the CFO allocates to the FP&A Manager to complete (e.g. overhead recovery and overhead resourcing reviews). 

The FP&A Manager is to remain positive relationships with ELT members and provide analytical support as directed by the CFO or Finance & Admin Leader. 




Qualifications 

Minimum level of knowledge/skills/training required to carry out the job: 

CPA or CA qualification required

Bachelor degree in Accounting, Finance, Commerce, Economics or equivalent required

Masters degree in Accounting, Finance or Business Administration preferred

Demonstrated capacity to build, foster, and maintain effective relationships with internal stakeholders at a senior level and adept at fostering cross-functional cooperation and stakeholder alignment.

Proven initiative, problem solving ability and strong work ethic with the capacity to establish priorities, manage deadlines and work independently under broad direction and as part of a multidisciplinary team.

Illustrated ability to provide guidance, and mentoring to junior colleagues to support their professional development.

Advanced Microsoft excel skills for forecast modelling analytics and data management.

Work Experience

Considered necessary to do the job effectively:

Minimum of 5 to 10 years full time experience in financing and accounting

Working collaboratively in a small team environment

Turosi Pty Ltd is a privately owned Company with facilities in Victoria, Queensland, and NSW, providing a full range of raw and cooked food solutions across a range of proteins and foods to the retail and food service.

An exciting career opportunity exists for a Commercial Analyst. Based in the northern suburbs and reporting to the Finance Manager Sales and NPD, the role will support the Commercial Finance team by partnering with the business on Commercial, Controlling and Reporting matters, providing data analytics & reporting and supporting the administration of financial systems.

Creating reports based on the collected data and interpretations.

Review price and margins and recommend action to improve profitability.

Provide support for strategic decision making.

The Ideal Candidate for this role: 

A tertiary qualification in accounting or similar subject from a recognised University

High level numeracy with attention to detail and accuracy with figures

Advanced level of computer literacy and Microsoft Excel skills

Exposure to ERP and BI systems

A Go-getter, positive, and keen to learn attitude.

Ability to effectively communicate to non-finance staff.

Why Join Us?
This role offers the opportunity to work with a large, established company. You will be part of a supportive and dynamic team where you can make a significant impact to the Commercial Finance team. An attractive salary package is available for the right candidate.

If this role sounds like you, send your CV through today by clicking the Apply Button

About the role:

The Senior Consultant, Data Modelling is responsible for providing expert guidance and support in designing, implementing, and optimising data architecture frameworks that align with the organisation's strategic objectives. The Senior Consultant, Data Modelling plays a key role in managing data model design and implementation, advising stakeholders, and driving improvements in data management practices.

As a Senior Consultant, Data Modelling you will:

Design, optimise, and maintain scalable conceptual, logical, and physical data models, schemas, and architectures to ensure that organisational data is organised, accessible, and secure across systems. Monitor and assess performance, identify areas for improvement and implement necessary changes.
Ensure data models align with the organisation’s strategic objectives and support its academic, research, and administrative functions.
Work collaboratively with teams to develop, establish, maintain and publish data standards, Data Platform data models, data dictionaries and associated metadata.
Define extract and import logic to create the transformations (ETL or ELT) into and within the Data Platform and support resolution of related workflow and data verification process matters
Manage the data modelling component of data architecture projects, ensuring they are completed on time and meet organisational requirements.
Support the integration of data across various systems, ensuring consistency and reliability of data, contribute to master data management (MDM) mapping to enhance data alignment and quality across platforms.                                                                                                                                                                    

To be successful, you’ll have:

Postgraduate qualifications and extensive relevant experience; or
Extensive experience and management expertise; or
An equivalent combination of relevant experience and/or education/training.
Experience in data modelling, with a proven track record of service delivery to meet client expectations.
Experience in designing and implementing Inmon and Kimball style data models and frameworks.
Experience with Erwin Data Modelling tool.

Here's how to apply: 

Please submit your updated resume and a short cover letter outlining your skills and experience. 

For a confidential discussion regarding this role, please contact Rodney Wheeler (Senior Manager, Data Architecture) via email at r.wheeler@deakin.edu.au

For a copy of the position description, please see below:

 Senior Consultant, Data Modelling - HEW 9_ PD.pdf

Applications for this position close at 11.55pm on Thursday 6th November.

Permanent opportunity
Sydney location
Directly influence the Group’s largest commercial partners




We are Woolworths Group

We are Woolworths Group. 200,000+ bright minds, passionate hearts and unique perspectives connected by a shared Purpose – ‘to create better experiences together for a better tomorrow.’ It’s that Purpose that fuels our ambition to explore new ideas, make brave commitments and innovate better ways to meet the food and everyday needs of more than 24 million customers every week. 

If you’re excited to turn today’s blue sky thinking into a better tomorrow for future generations, you’ll find yourself supported and enriched in a dynamic, inclusive and empowering workplace that reflects the diverse communities we serve. With a culture of genuine care, a flexible approach to work and opportunities across the group to grow your career and make a meaningful impact, the possibilities for what we can achieve together are endless.




Welcome to PartnerCo

PartnerCo is responsible for the active oversight and management of Woolworths Group strategic external partners and works across the full spectrum of the Group to ensure each partnership delivers valuable commercial outcomes.

This role sits within the PartnerCo team as part of the Group Finance function. It supports the Head of Commercial Partnerships. 




The Opportunity

Strategic partnerships are critical to creating better experiences for our customers. The PartnerCo team manages the overarching relationships with our most strategic external partners as well as works across internal Retail and Group Platforms to unlock mutual strategic and financial value.

The Commercial Manager, PartnerCo role exists to provide the analytical rigour, structured problem-solving, and commercial horsepower required to execute our complex partnership strategies. This role focuses on bringing strategic thinking to commercial opportunities and challenges, and is instrumental in driving key workstreams and managing stakeholders to deliver tangible outcomes.




What you’ll do

This role is key to managing some of the Group’s most significant and complex commercial partnerships because it directly enables the realisation of the objectives of these partnerships and manages the associated risks .

Conduct deep-dive commercial and financial analysis
Inject strategic and innovative thinking to solve key partnership questions
Project manage key projects and work streams end-to-end
Translate complex partnership dynamics into compelling presentations, reports, and briefing documents for senior leadership and partner-facing forums
Bring strong relationship management skills to influence to a wide range of internal and external stakeholders to operationalise value creation
Strategically manage complex, cross-functional commercial initiatives by balancing detailed analysis with executive-level communication and influencing diverse stakeholders to deliver timely, high-quality outcomes.




What you’ll bring

3-5 years in a commercial and analytical role within a top-tier strategy consulting or accounting firm, investment bank, or comparable corporate development/M&A team.
Commercial and financial acumen, analytical and strategic problem solving skills, project management, stakeholder engagement, strong written and oral communication and ability to influence at all levels of the organisation, high learning agility.
Advanced proficiency in Google Suite and/or Microsoft Office (Slides/PowerPoint, Sheets/Excel).
Proven ability to influence a diverse range of stakeholders across different business units and partner organisations.
Ability to navigate the ambiguity and complexities of large-scale, multi-layered commercial agreements.




What you’ll experience

Hybrid Flexibility: Blend of in-office engagement with work-from-home opportunities for a balanced work week.
A global business with endless career possibilities around every corner and across every discipline – with valuable exposure to a vast and exciting business network.
Team discounts across our range of Woolworths Group brands you know and love and a robust rewards program that celebrates and incentivises purpose-driven work.
12 weeks paid parental leave for primary caregivers plus paid superannuation for up to 12 months while the Team Member is on parental leave - eligible from the first day of employment




Everyone belongs at Woolworths Group 

As one of the largest employers in Australia and New Zealand, we aim to create a truly inclusive workplace where everyone feels that they belong, can be their best selves, and reach their full potential.

Diversity, equity, inclusion, and belonging are key to realising our purpose of better together for a better tomorrow. We recognise the value our team’s diversity brings to our business, customers, and communities and that teams with diverse experiences and backgrounds enrich our group and are better able to innovate and solve problems. 

Woolworths Group is an inclusive, team-first company and we value all skills and experiences. If you meet some, but not all of the requirements, we encourage you to submit your application.

Ad Text:
Who We Are

In Melbourne, water is essential to our way of life.

As caretakers for Melbourne’s water cycle, we care for water, life and land throughout Melbourne: both its people and its biodiversity.

Each time you drink from the tap, flush a toilet, run through a backyard sprinkler, or kayak down the Yarra, we’re there. Primed and ready, quietly delivering some of the world’s cleanest water for over five million residents and wildlife that call Melbourne home, just as we have for over 130 years.

If you value making it count, diving in with curiosity, and doing what’s right, you're in the right place.

About The Role

Reporting to the Manager, Commercial Systems, this full-time, fixed-term role ending October 2026, is part of the Finance team at Melbourne Water. As the Commercial Data Analytics, you’ll be responsible for using data to support senior leaders with practical advice and insights on business performance. Your work will help guide decisions that improve financial and operational outcomes across the organisation.

Improve commercial performance by conducting detailed analytics and identifying areas for improvement in the cost structure of the business as well as identifying new opportunities through data with a focus on bottom line improvement
Provision of in-house analytics services and development of a pipeline of work from within the business and other enabling functions of analysis services
Drive analytics of organisational goals with a view of guiding goal teams to meaningfully measure their outputs
Provide senior leaders with expert knowledge and experience of current business processes, risks, requirements and deliverables
Assist the finance team in coaching and mentoring the business through change
Ensure business risks are identified and adequately managed in the identified solution
Champion employees user experience and the practicality of data-led solutions
Constructively challenge the status quo and inspire new thinking
About You
Tertiary degree in Computer Science, Economics, Engineering, Finance, Mathematics or related disciplines.
Experience and expertise gained through a similar position.
Proven and demonstrable experience working with and deriving insights from large and complex data sets via ETLs, Microsoft Excel, Power BI, Power Query, etc.
Understanding of accounting, finance and financial modelling concepts.
Experience developing team and function data and analytics capability.
Highly developed data analytics, accounting, finance and financial modelling technical leadership skills.
Expertise in data analysis, analytics and visualisation tools with a focus on Power BI and Microsoft Excel.
Knowledge of the data analytics process, from data understanding, cleansing, transformation, interpretation to presentation.

At Melbourne Water this role is internally known as Commercial Analytics Lead. We have advertised this role as Commercial Data Analytics to closely align interests to similar positions held in the market. 

For more information, please review the attached position description: Commercial Analytics Lead.pdf

Why Join Us

At Melbourne Water, we care about water and all life that springs from it.

Our people are fuelled by passion, and with safety at the forefront, we have an unwavering sense of purpose, and are on a mission to protect every Melburnian’s way of life, one drop at a time.

We walk the talk when it comes to flexible working – but that’s not all. Our culture of purpose, safety, results, and learning permeates everything we do. We're dedicated to doing what's right, and this commitment extends to the meaningful work we do in a supportive and inclusive culture that encourages you to make the most of your talents.

Our long-standing commitment to Diversity, Inclusion, and Belonging means that Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, LGBTIQ+ individuals, people living with disability, mature age and young jobseekers from all cultures can apply with confidence knowing they are safe, affirmed, and celebrated.

If you’re curious, action-orientated, outcomes-focused, and care deeply for public resources, community, and the environment, we'd love to receive an application and learn if you could be a great fit.

How To Apply

Click the 'Apply Now' button below and complete our online application form.

Job Title: Senior Range & Space Transformation & Governance Manager
Ad Text:
We’ve been trusted to serve Aussie communities since 1914 and grown to become a top 30-listed on the ASX with over 115,000 team members and a portfolio of iconic brands. At Coles Group, you’ll not only get to make a difference to millions of Aussie lives—you’ll also get to see your impact.

About the team

Our Commercial team is a large, but a close-knit group of trading experts, who are ready to shape the future of Coles. We pride ourselves on the long-lasting supplier relationships we build, the new ideas we develop and how passionately we work to help Australian eat and live better every day. And the best part? We’re all so different. We bring diversity of thought, backgrounds, and experience to every Business Unit across Coles Supermarkets and Liquor.

About the Role


Are you ready to shape the future of retail range and space strategy in one of Australia’s most dynamic retail environments?

We’re seeking a strategic, data-curious leader to join our Commercial team as a Senior Range & Space Transformation & Governance Manager. This is a high-impact role that leads three distinct streams and their dedicated teams

Insights & Analytics, who shape the delivery of our strategic data. They deliver strategic data insights, build dashboards, and support ad hoc queries.
Transformation & Governance, who manage our range review schedules and drive continuous improvement.
Transformation & Delivery, who execute key strategic priorities and shape future range strategies.

This is more than a leadership role - it’s an opportunity to influence the future of retail through innovation, collaboration, and customer-first thinking. You’ll be part of a team that’s building cutting-edge tools and frameworks, with the autonomy to shape how we work and the impact we deliver.

You will also;

Define how we deliver tailored, customer-centric ranges across our store network
Drive strategic initiatives that simplify and innovate how we build, manage, and execute range and space across the business
Partner with Category Managers and senior stakeholders to align plans with customer missions, pricing strategies, and operational capabilities
Own and evolve the end-to-end range review process, embedding governance frameworks that ensure transparency, compliance, and efficiency
Shape the delivery of strategic insights through advanced analytics, including PowerBI dashboards and Snowflake migration, to provide real-time visibility and support smarter decisions
Deliver data-led storytelling to senior stakeholders in a compelling and easy to understand manner
Help build and leverage some of the most advanced range and space tools in Australia
Lead a team of four direct reports, fostering a culture of curiosity, collaboration, and continuous improvement


About you and your skills 


Our ideal candidate is a strategic thinker with a deep understanding of retail or FMCG environments, who thrives on solving complex problems and driving transformation. They are naturally curious about data, with the ability to translate insights into actionable strategies that enhance customer experience and commercial outcomes. With proven leadership experience, they can inspire and guide a diverse team across analytics, governance, and delivery streams. They bring a strong background in process optimisation, continuous improvement, and stakeholder engagement, and are confident presenting strategic narratives to senior leaders. Above all, they are passionate about building future-fit solutions and frameworks that shape how range and space are delivered across the business.

You will also ideally have;

Proven experience in retail, FMCG, or commercial roles within a centralised function
Strong background in strategy, transformation, governance, and process design
Ability to lead complex projects and deliver sustainable outcomes
Strategic mindset with the ability to craft compelling narratives for senior stakeholders
Passion for data, curiosity to ask “why,” and the ability to dive deep into complex datasets
Experience with demand/resource planning tools or workforce management approaches
Proven experience leading a team including coaching, motivating, and building cross-functional collaboration
Familiarity with platforms like Blue Yonder and PowerBI is beneficial, but not essential

What’s in it for you?

Flexible working options: We know that work is only one part of your life, so we actively encourage a positive work-life balance and provide hybrid working options to help you achieve it.
Office perks: Take advantage of our gym facility and fitness classes, free parking, BBQ area, mini-Coles supermarket, fooderie hub where you can sample new products before they hit the shelves, school holiday program and so much more when you come in.
Discounts: Eligible team members receive 5% discount all year round on your Supermarket and Liquor online and in-store purchases. We also offer additional periods of double discount (10%) at various times throughout the year. As well as hotdeals exclusive to team members that translate into additional savings.
Reward through recognition: Give and receive recognition, linked to our Coles values, through our digital recognition platform ‘mythanks’. You can accumulate points to redeem in the online shop for exciting gifts and electronic gift cards from an extensive range of retailers.
Opportunities for learning and development: No matter where you start within our diverse business, you’ll have experiences, exposure, and education to satisfy you. Discover and explore a variety of career development programs and job-specific training.
Paid parental leave: We understand how important your life outside work is and offer permanent team members paid parental leave to support you in balancing work and family.
Investment in your future: Our annual team member share plan offer allows eligible team members to make regular pre-tax salary sacrifice deductions to purchase Coles Group shares.

About the recruitment process

We’re continuing to build a gender equitable team, and a culture that is just as diverse, inclusive and welcoming as the communities we serve. We are committed to creating a workplace that is safe and respectful for our team. We encourage applications from people of all ages, cultures (including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples), abilities, sexual orientation and gender identities.

We’re happy to adjust our recruitment process to support candidates with disability. For further information and additional contact details visit the ‘Our Recruitment Process’ section of our careers site or email inclusionrecruitment@coles.com.au

Challenger Limited is an ASX-listed investment management firm managing $123.9 billion in assets (as at 30 June 2025). Life with us is fast moving and always exciting. Together we’re driving to deliver our vision to provide our customers with financial security for a better retirement.

We achieve this goal by providing a work environment where people from diverse backgrounds, with a range of skills and experiences can contribute and succeed.

Finance Manager (FP&A) – Funds Management Business Performance 

We are looking for a strategic and collaborative Finance Manager (FP&A) to join our dynamic and engaged Business Performance & Analysis team.

This role offers strong career pathways due to its visibility, impact, and the opportunity to deliver meaningful outcomes in a supportive and inclusive environment. 

We offer a flexible hybrid working model based out of our Martin Place, Sydney CBD office — typically 3 days in-office and 2 days from home.

About the role

Reporting to the Head of Business Performance, you’ll play a key role in partnering with senior business and finance stakeholders to provide clear reporting and forecasting, offering insights that guide strategic choices and enable sustainable growth.

How you will make an impact

Support Business Growth

Prepare, consolidate, and deliver rolling monthly forecasts, annual budgeting, and planning outputs across Funds Management.

Link financial planning to strategic objectives and monitor KPIs to track progress.

Develop scenario plans to assess potential market changes and business impacts.

Partner with Senior Business Stakeholders

Run the management reporting process and deliver actionable insights to senior stakeholders.

Prepare variance and trend insights, scenario modelling, and performance commentary to guide informed decisions.

Translate complex financial data into clear narratives that inform decision-making.

Partner with Investor Relations and senior stakeholders to align insights and expectations and support investor releases.

Educate stakeholders on financial implications to support informed choices.

Support Growth and Relationships

Enhance sales profitability and expense insights that influence growth strategies and business outcomes 

Assist with financial transactions and financial due diligence opportunities

Mentor and guide junior team members

Innovation and Smart Solutions

Champion automation and the use of AI across finance platforms including Anaplan, Workiva, and Workday.

Continuously improve and innovate processes to enhance efficiency and insight delivery.

What you’ll bring to the table

You’re a CA/CPA-qualified finance professional. You’ve held a Finance Manager or Finance Business Partner role with full accountability for financial planning, reporting, and analysis (FP&A), and have delivered actionable insights that enable informed decisions.

You are a collaborative finance partner, with a genuine curiosity to uncover insights behind the numbers. You communicate clearly with senior stakeholders, present complex information effectively, and take an organised and solutions-focused approach to managing priorities and finding opportunities.

Some other things that will set you apart

Delivered end-to-end budgeting, forecasting, variance analysis, and management reporting. 

Strong business acumen and influencing skills to guide strategic conversations

Advanced Excel and strong technical skills with finance systems, and data tools. 

Familiarity with cloud-based platforms like Anaplan, Workiva, Workday, or Power BI (preferred). 

Why Challenger?

**What’s the role?**

**The Team**

+ Act as a strategic learning advisor on internal systems, identifying opportunities for capability uplift and process optimisation.

+ Lead the design, development, and seamless rollout of learning supporting system capability uplift

+ Develop comprehensive training strategies and design frameworks for new system implementations.

+ Manage complex systems learning projects from inception to successful deployment.

+ Forge strong, collaborative relationships with stakeholders across all business functions to facilitate effective system adoption.

+ Support the testing of systems to ensure functionality and data accuracy.

**Who are you?**

+ A tertiary qualification in Business, Information Technology, Learning and Development, Project Management, or a related discipline.

+ Demonstrated experience in systems implementation, business analysis, project management, learning strategy, or capability development within a complex, multi-functional organisational environment.

+ A proven track record of successfully leading learning design and rollout of significant technology initiatives

+ Experience in applying instructional design principles and developing learning strategies for complex technology rollouts is highly regarded.

+ A strong understanding of diverse business processes and cross-functional data flows.

+ Project management, analytical, problem-solving, and stakeholder management skills

+ **Exclusively ours** – Access to publications and products from across the News Corp family

+ **Health & wellbeing** – Advice, support and facilities for healthy minds and bodies (including an onsite gym at our Adelaide, Brisbane & Sydney offices)

+ **Time off** – News offers a range of leave options to support your personal needs and moments that matter in life: Parental leave, Birthday leave, Volunteer leave, Career break and Compassionate leave.

+ **Helping you grow** – Development opportunities (including diversity and inclusion – focused education series) and recognition

+ **Financial wellbeing** – Support on making the most of your money

+ **Perks & discounts** – Exclusive offers across a range of products and services

+ **Giving back** – Make a difference to our communities.

Job Description


Strategic Leadership:

Be able to effectively communicate the value of AI/ ML solutions to business users and brokers

Strong communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to influence and engage stakeholders at all levels

Job Title: Director of Strategic Planning, Streaming & Broadcast
Ad Text:
Company Description


Nine is Australia’s largest locally owned media company. Working at Nine, you’ll have access to a unique range of experiences and opportunities, helping drive the success of the country’s most trusted television, radio, digital and publishing brands. 

Our content reaches almost every Australian - meaning what we do has real impact. We bring people together, celebrate the big moments, and capture the everyday ones.

Some of our most beloved brands have been part of Australian life for generations, and others - new on the scene - have already found their place firmly in our lives. We’re evolving and we need people like you to bring new ideas, innovate and make your mark.

Job Description


This is a high-impact leadership role within the Strategy department for Nine's Streaming & Broadcast division. Reporting to the Chief Strategy Officer, Streaming and Broadcast, you'll serve as a commercial engine for the division by leading strategic planning processes and ensuring alignment with Nine's corporate strategy and financial goals.

The Strategy department drives strategic and operational planning by converting data and consumer insights into action. This work shapes the division's investment decisions, competitive market value proposition, pricing, and product.

Working closely with the leadership team, you will develop long-term business plans, identify new growth opportunities, and create robust business cases for strategic initiatives.

Day to day, you will:

Lead strategic planning processes, including annual planning, new growth identification, investment reviews, and market intelligence.
Develop robust business cases for key strategic initiatives, outlining market potential and financial projections, while coordinating alignment across the leadership team.
Collaborate effectively with a wide range of stakeholders, including other leaders within Streaming & Broadcast, as well as Finance, Data, Group Strategy, and others.
Develop and manage the valuation methodology for content acquisition and commissioning (sport, news, entertainment).
Lead the strategic insights function to embed actionable, data-driven insights into business cases, decision-making, and operations.
Lead detailed analysis to unlock value and deduplicate interconnected revenue/cost implications across business units.
Lead assembly of MD, CEO, and Board materials for investment options, budget, performance, and strategic initiatives.

Please submit your resume and cover letter by Friday, October 31st.

Qualifications


What you'll bring:

Experience in senior strategic leadership roles, preferably in media, technology, or a related consumer-facing industry.
Strong commercial skillset, with hands-on capability in building business cases, budgeting processes, and financial analysis.
Proven capability in creating high-impact strategic narratives and preparation of board-level presentation materials.
Experience leading insight teams and transforming the use of data to drive decision-making
Proven experience leading and collaborating across a matrixed organisation.
A collaborative and adaptable working style with strong interpersonal skills.
Experience leading sports and/or other content rights investment initiatives (beneficial).

Additional Information


How we work

At Nine, our flexible work options vary by role and team. Depending on the position, this may include flexible hours, hybrid work, or part-time arrangements. We welcome discussing your flexibility needs during the hiring process - just ask the Talent Acquisition team. 

Our employee benefits include:

18 weeks paid parental leave with no distinction between primary and secondary carers.
Access to 'Employee Exclusives' program - a way of getting closer to our incredible brands, offering unique experiences, behind-the-scenes access, and awesome perks.
Digital newspaper subscription to our mastheads.
Annual gift voucher for Stan subscription.

More info at Nine Careers.

Our Commitment to Diversity and Inclusion:

We're committed to a safe, respectful and inclusive Nine. From day one, you'll be encouraged to bring your whole self to work and will be supported to perform at your best.

We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people with disabilities, and of all ages, genders, nationalities, backgrounds and cultures as we recognise the importance and value of diverse perspectives. Should you require any adjustments to the recruitment process, please advise us when you apply.

Work rights: Please note to apply for this role you must already have the right to lawfully work and live in Australia.
